{
  "text": "According to the sensor noise characteristics, the weights of the accelerometer-magnetometer combination are 0.9 and 0.1, respectively; while for the accelerometer-magnetometer-GNSS combination, the weights are chosen as 0.474, 0.05 and 0.474, respectively. The reference vector of the magnetometer is determined by the initial GNSS positioning results with the IGRF model [CITATION_1] . By making use of algorithms including QUEST, FLAE, OLEQ and SOLEQ, the computation results are summarized in Figures 8 and 9 .",
